Chapter.Article:
Obliged entities must take measures proportionate to their risks, nature,
and size to ensure that:
(a) all relevant employees are aware of applicable AML/CFT provisions,
    including data protection requirements;
(b) employees participate in ongoing, specialised training programmes to
    help them recognise ML/TF operations and know how to proceed when
    such operations are identified;
(c) employees have access to up-to-date information on current ML/TF
    methods and indicators for recognising suspicious transactions;
(d) where practicable, timely feedback on the effectiveness and follow-up
    of their ML/TF reports is provided;
(e) where applicable, the member of the management board responsible for
    AML/CFT compliance implementation is identified.

Annexes.Annex:
Non-exhaustive list:
(i)   the purpose of an account or business relationship;
(ii)  the level of assets to be deposited or the size of transactions;
(iii) the regularity or duration of the business relationship.
